message: Focus on cooking simple combinations. First, combine a protein with a grain, then use the stove; this reliably creates an item worth 40. Next, combine any raw vegetables, then cook them with the stove to get another item worth 40. Be cautious when combining two already-cooked multi-component items, as this often creates 'overcomplicated' dishes with a value of 0. However, if you have two *simple* cooked ingredients (like a cooked egg and a cooked vegetable), combining them might yield a high score (60). Avoid using the water tool on cooked items, and do not re-cook items that are already complex or have been cooked multiple times, as this usually leads to negative values. If an item becomes 'overcomplicated' with 0 value, it's usually best to submit and start fresh.
